46 +     @State(Scope.Benchmark)
47 +     public static class ReadState extends JsonAuditEventHandlerWriteBenchmarkTest.DefaultState  {
48 +         private int counter;
49 +         private String[] identifiers;
50 +
51 +         /**
52 +          * Gets a pseudo-random audit event identifier.
53 +          *
54 +          * @return identifier
55 +          */
56 +         String getRandomIdentifier() {
57 +             // NOTE: it doesn't matter that the counter will be updated by multiple thread concurrently
58 +             return identifiers[++counter % PRE_POPULATED_EVENT_COUNT];
59 +         }
60 +
61 +         @Override
62 +         protected void afterStartup() throws Exception {
63 +             // pre-populate with data and store generated IDs
64 +             identifiers = new String[PRE_POPULATED_EVENT_COUNT];
65 +             for (int i = 0; i < PRE_POPULATED_EVENT_COUNT; ++i) {
66 +                 final String id = String.format("%010d", i);
67 +                 final JsonValue event = json(object(
68 +                         field("_id", id), field("timestamp", id), field("transactionId", id)));
69 +                 identifiers[i] = handler.publishEvent(null, ACCESS, event).get().getId();
70 +             }
71 +
72 +             // flush the underlying file buffer, after all test-events have been published
73 +             final ActionRequest actionRequest = Requests.newActionRequest(ACCESS, FLUSH_FILE_ACTION_NAME)
74 +                     .setAdditionalParameter(ACTION_PARAM_TARGET_HANDLER, "json");
75 +             handler.handleAction(null, ACCESS, actionRequest).getOrThrow();
76 +
77 +             // shuffle ordering of IDs, to simulate random access
78 +             // https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fisher%E2%80%93Yates_shuffle#The_modern_algorithm
79 +             final Random random = ThreadLocalRandom.current();
80 +             for (int i = PRE_POPULATED_EVENT_COUNT - 1; i > 0; --i) {
81 +                 final int index = random.nextInt(i + 1);
82 +                 final String s = identifiers[index];
83 +                 identifiers[index] = identifiers[i];
84 +                 identifiers[i] = s;
85 +             }
86 +
87 +             // sleep to make sure async-publisher-thread finished all work
88 +             Thread.sleep(1_000);
89 +         }
90 +     }

112 +         if (jsonFilePath == null) {
113 +             return newResourceException(NOT_FOUND, "Topic not found: " + topic).asPromise();
114 +         }

128 +         } catch (Exception e) {

133 +     @Override
134 +     public Promise<QueryResponse, ResourceException> queryEvents(final Context context, final String topic,
135 +             final QueryRequest query, final QueryResourceHandler handler) {
136 +         final Path jsonFilePath = jsonFileWriter.getTopicFilePath(topic);
137 +         if (jsonFilePath == null) {
138 +             return newResourceException(NOT_FOUND, "Topic not found: " + topic).asPromise();
139 +         }
140 +         final QueryFilter<JsonPointer> queryFilter = query.getQueryFilter();
141 +         int results = 0;
142 +         String line;
143 +         try (final BufferedReader reader = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(
144 +                 Files.newInputStream(jsonFilePath), StandardCharsets.UTF_8))) {
145 +             line = reader.readLine();
146 +             while (line != null) {
147 +                 final JsonValue event = new JsonValue(OBJECT_MAPPER.readValue(line, Map.class));
148 +                 if (queryFilter.accept(JSONVALUE_FILTER_VISITOR, event)) {
149 +                     ++results;
150 +                     final ResourceResponse resourceResponse =
151 +                             newResourceResponse(event.get(FIELD_CONTENT_ID).asString(), null, event);
152 +                     if (!handler.handleResource(resourceResponse)) {
153 +                         break;
154 +                     }
155 +                 }
156 +                 line = reader.readLine();
157 +             }
158 +         } catch (Exception e) {
159 +             return newResourceException(INTERNAL_ERROR, "Failed to read json file: " + jsonFilePath, e).asPromise();
160 +         }
161 +         return newQueryResponse(null, CountPolicy.EXACT, results).asPromise();
162 +     }
163 +
164 +     @Override
165 +     public Promise<ActionResponse, ResourceException> handleAction(final Context context, final String topic,
166 +             final ActionRequest request) {
167 +         final Path jsonFilePath = jsonFileWriter.getTopicFilePath(topic);
168 +         if (jsonFilePath == null) {
169 +             return newResourceException(NOT_FOUND, "Topic not found: " + topic).asPromise();
170 +         }
171 +         try {
172 +             switch (request.getAction()) {
173 +             case ROTATE_FILE_ACTION_NAME:
174 +                 if (!jsonFileWriter.rotateFile(topic)) {
175 +                     return newResourceException(BAD_REQUEST, "Rotation not enabled").asPromise();
176 +                 }
177 +                 break;
178 +             case FLUSH_FILE_ACTION_NAME:
179 +                 jsonFileWriter.flushFileBuffer(topic);
180 +                 break;
181 +             default:
182 +                 return newResourceException(BAD_REQUEST, "Unsupported action: " + request.getAction()).asPromise();
183 +             }
184 +             return newActionResponse(json(object(field("status", "OK")))).asPromise();
185 +         } catch (Exception e) {
186 +             return newResourceException(INTERNAL_ERROR, "Failed to invoke action", e).asPromise();
187 +         }
188 +     }

147 +      * @throws InterruptedException thread interrupted while blocking on a full queue
148 +      */
149 +     boolean rotateFile(final String topic) throws InterruptedException {
150 +         if (queueConsumer.isRotationEnabled()) {
151 +             queue.put(new QueueEntry(topic, QueueEntry.ROTATE_FILE_ENTRY));
152 +             return true;
153 +         }
154 +         return false;
155 +     }
156 +
157 +     /**
158 +      * Requests an unscheduled buffer-flush of the underlying JSON audit file, which is useful for testing.
159 +      * <p>
160 +      * The flush will happen after all preexisting events in the queue have been processed.
161 +      *
162 +      * @param topic Event topic
163 +      * @throws InterruptedException thread interrupted while blocking on a full queue
164 +      */
165 +     void flushFileBuffer(final String topic) throws InterruptedException {
166 +         queue.put(new QueueEntry(topic, QueueEntry.FLUSH_FILE_ENTRY));
167 +     }
168 +
169 +     /**
170 +      * Gets the current log-file for the given topic.
171 +      *
172 +      * @param topic Topic name (case-sensitive)

174 +      */
175 +     Path getTopicFilePath(final String topic) {

178 +     }
179 +
180 +     /**
181 +      * A single audit-event entry.
182 +      */
183 +     private static class QueueEntry {
184 +
185 +         static final byte[] ROTATE_FILE_ENTRY = new byte[0];
186 +         static final byte[] FLUSH_FILE_ENTRY = new byte[0];
187 +
188 +         private final String topic;
189 +         private final byte[] event;
190 +
191 +         /**
192 +          * Creates a new audit-event batch entry.
193 +          *
194 +          * @param topic Event topic
195 +          * @param event Event JSON payload
196 +          */
197 +         QueueEntry(final String topic, final byte[] event) {
198 +             this.topic = checkNotNull(topic);
199 +             this.event = checkNotNull(event);
200 +         }
201 +
202 +         boolean isRotateEntry() {
203 +             return event == ROTATE_FILE_ENTRY;
204 +         }
205 +
206 +         boolean isFlushEntry() {
207 +             return event == FLUSH_FILE_ENTRY;
208 +         }
209 +     }
210 +
211 +     /**
212 +      * Consumer of the audit-event batch queue, which can be scheduled to run periodically. This class is not
213 +      * thread-safe, and is intended to be run by a single thread.
214 +      */
215 +     private static final class QueueConsumer implements Runnable {
216 +
217 +         private static final int BATCH_SIZE = 5000;
218 +         private static final int OUTPUT_BUF_INITIAL_SIZE = 16 * 1024;
219 +         private static final byte[] NEWLINE_UTF_8_BYTES = "\n".getBytes(UTF_8);
220 +
221 +         private final boolean flushOnShutdown;
222 +         private final boolean rotationEnabled;
223 +         private final boolean hasRotationOrRetentionPolicies;
224 +         private final List<RotationPolicy> rotationPolicies;
225 +         private final List<RetentionPolicy> retentionPolicies;
226 +         private final Set<File> filesToDelete;
227 +         private final BlockingQueue<QueueEntry> queue;
228 +         private final ScheduledExecutorService scheduler;
229 +         private final Map<String, TopicEntry> topicEntryMap;
230 +         private final List<QueueEntry> drainList;
231 +
232 +         private volatile boolean shutdown;
233 +
234 +         /**
235 +          * Creates a {@code QueueConsumer}.
236 +          *
237 +          * @param fileNameSuffix Log file-name suffix
238 +          * @param topics Supported topics
239 +          * @param configuration Configuration
240 +          * @param flushOnShutdown When {@code true}, the queue will be flushed on shutdown and when {@code false},
241 +          * items in the queue will be dropped
242 +          * @param queue Audit-event queue
243 +          * @param scheduler This runnable's scheduler
244 +          */
245 +         private QueueConsumer(final String fileNameSuffix, final Set<String> topics,
246 +                 final JsonAuditEventHandlerConfiguration configuration, final boolean flushOnShutdown,
247 +                 final BlockingQueue<QueueEntry> queue, final ScheduledExecutorService scheduler) {
248 +             this.queue = queue;
249 +             this.scheduler = scheduler;
250 +             this.flushOnShutdown = flushOnShutdown;
251 +             drainList = new ArrayList<>(BATCH_SIZE);
252 +             rotationEnabled = configuration.getFileRotation().isRotationEnabled();
253 +             rotationPolicies = configuration.getFileRotation().buildRotationPolicies();
254 +             retentionPolicies = configuration.getFileRetention().buildRetentionPolicies();
255 +             hasRotationOrRetentionPolicies = (rotationEnabled && !rotationPolicies.isEmpty())
256 +                     || !retentionPolicies.isEmpty();
257 +             filesToDelete = new HashSet<>();
258 +
259 +             // build map of topic files
260 +             final Map<String, TopicEntry> topicEntryMap = new HashMap<>();
261 +             for (final String topic : topics) {
262 +                 final String fileName = topic + '.' + fileNameSuffix;
263 +                 topicEntryMap.put(topic, new TopicEntry(fileName, configuration));
264 +             }
265 +             this.topicEntryMap = Collections.unmodifiableMap(topicEntryMap);
266 +         }
267 +
268 +         /**
269 +          * Informs queue consumer that shutdown has been triggered, and when {@code flushOnShutdown} is enabled,
270 +          * blocks until all events have been flushed from the queue.
271 +          */
272 +         void shutdown() {
273 +             if (!shutdown) {
274 +                 shutdown = true;
275 +
276 +                 if (flushOnShutdown) {
277 +                     // flush requested, so block in an non-cancelable way
278 +                     boolean interrupted = false;
279 +                     while (!scheduler.isTerminated()) {
280 +                         try {
281 +                             scheduler.awaitTermination(1L, TimeUnit.MINUTES);
282 +                         } catch (InterruptedException e) {
283 +                             interrupted = true;
284 +                         }
285 +                     }
286 +                     if (interrupted) {
287 +                         Thread.currentThread().interrupt();
288 +                     }
289 +                 }
290 +             }
291 +         }
292 +
293 +         @Override
294 +         public void run() {
295 +             if (!shutdown) {
296 +                 // following loop will run at least once, even if queue is empty, so that rotation policies will run
297 +                 do {
298 +                     writeEvents();
299 +                 } while (!queue.isEmpty() && !shutdown);
300 +             }
301 +
302 +             if (shutdown) {
303 +                 // we shutdown this runnable's scheduler here, so that we can guarantee that flush will proceed
304 +                 scheduler.shutdown();
305 +                 try {
306 +                     if (flushOnShutdown) {
307 +                         while (!queue.isEmpty()) {
308 +                             writeEvents();
309 +                         }
310 +                         for (final TopicEntry topicEntry : topicEntryMap.values()) {
311 +                             topicEntry.flush();
312 +                         }
313 +                     }
314 +                 } finally {
315 +                     closeSilently(topicEntryMap.values());
316 +                 }
317 +             }
318 +         }
319 +
320 +         private void writeEvents() {
321 +             drainList.clear();
322 +             try {
323 +                 // handle one batch of events
324 +                 final int n = queue.drainTo(drainList, BATCH_SIZE);
325 +                 for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
326 +                     final QueueEntry entry = drainList.get(i);
327 +                     final TopicEntry topicEntry = topicEntryMap.get(entry.topic);
328 +                     if (topicEntry == null) {
329 +                         logger.warn("Unrecognised topic: " + entry.topic);
330 +                     } else {
331 +                         if (entry.isRotateEntry()) {
332 +                             topicEntry.rotateNow();
333 +                         } else if (entry.isFlushEntry()) {
334 +                             topicEntry.flush();
335 +                         } else {
336 +                             topicEntry.write(entry.event);
337 +                         }
338 +                     }
339 +                 }
340 +
341 +                 if (hasRotationOrRetentionPolicies) {
342 +                     // enforce rotation and/or retention policies for all topic files
343 +                     for (final TopicEntry topicEntry : topicEntryMap.values()) {
344 +                         topicEntry.rotateIfNeeded();
345 +                     }
346 +                 }
347 +             } catch (IOException e) {
348 +                 logger.error("JSON file write failed", e);
349 +             } catch (Exception e) {
350 +                 logger.error("Unexpected failure", e);
351 +             }
352 +         }
353 +
354 +         /**
355 +          * Checks if rotation is enabled.
356 +          *
357 +          * @return {@code true} if rotation is enabled and {@code false} otherwise
358 +          */
359 +         boolean isRotationEnabled() {
360 +             return rotationEnabled;
361 +         }
362 +
363 +         /**
364 +          * Represents state for a single topic audit-file.
365 +          */
366 +         private class TopicEntry implements RotatableObject, Closeable {
367 +             private static final int FILE_BUFFER_THRESHOLD = 8 * 1024;
368 +
369 +             private final Path filePath;
370 +             private final FileNamingPolicy fileNamingPolicy;
371 +             private final ByteBufferOutputStream outputStream;
372 +             private DateTime lastRotationTime;
373 +             private FileChannel fileChannel;
374 +             private long positionInFile;
375 +
376 +             TopicEntry(final String fileName, final JsonAuditEventHandlerConfiguration configuration) {
377 +                 try {
378 +                     outputStream = new ByteBufferOutputStream(ByteBuffer.allocateDirect(OUTPUT_BUF_INITIAL_SIZE));
379 +
380 +                     final Path directoryPath = Paths.get(configuration.getLogDirectory());
381 +                     if (Files.notExists(directoryPath)) {
382 +                         Files.createDirectory(directoryPath);
383 +                     }
384 +                     filePath = directoryPath.resolve(fileName);
385 +                     if (Files.notExists(filePath)) {
386 +                         fileChannel = FileChannel.open(filePath, StandardOpenOption.CREATE_NEW,
387 +                                 StandardOpenOption.WRITE);
388 +                     } else {
389 +                         fileChannel = FileChannel.open(filePath, StandardOpenOption.WRITE);
390 +                         positionInFile = fileChannel.size();
391 +                     }
392 +
393 +                     final File currentFile = filePath.toFile();
394 +                     fileNamingPolicy = configuration.getFileRotation().buildTimeStampFileNamingPolicy(currentFile);
395 +
396 +                     final long lastModified = currentFile.lastModified();
397 +                     this.lastRotationTime = lastModified > 0
398 +                             ? new DateTime(lastModified, DateTimeZone.UTC)
399 +                             : DateTime.now(DateTimeZone.UTC);
400 +                 } catch (IOException e) {
401 +                     throw new RuntimeException("Failed to create or open file", e);
402 +                 }
403 +             }
404 +
405 +             void write(final byte[] bytes) throws IOException {
406 +                 // newline delimited JSON with UTF-8 character encoding
407 +                 outputStream.write(bytes);
408 +                 outputStream.write(NEWLINE_UTF_8_BYTES);
409 +                 if (outputStream.byteBuffer().position() >= FILE_BUFFER_THRESHOLD) {
410 +                     outputStream.byteBuffer().flip();
411 +                     try {
412 +                         // write buffer to file
413 +                         positionInFile += fileChannel.write(outputStream.byteBuffer(), positionInFile);
414 +                     } finally {
415 +                         outputStream.clear();
416 +                     }
417 +                 }
418 +             }
419 +
420 +             void flush() {
421 +                 if (outputStream.byteBuffer().position() != 0) {
422 +                     // write buffer to file
423 +                     outputStream.byteBuffer().flip();
424 +                     try {
425 +                         positionInFile += fileChannel.write(outputStream.byteBuffer(), positionInFile);
426 +                     } catch (IOException e) {
427 +                         logger.error("Failed to flush file buffer", e);
428 +                     } finally {
429 +                         outputStream.clear();
430 +                     }
431 +                 }
432 +             }
433 +
434 +             @Override
435 +             public long getBytesWritten() {
436 +                 return positionInFile;
437 +             }
438 +
439 +             @Override
440 +             public DateTime getLastRotationTime() {
441 +                 return lastRotationTime;
442 +             }
443 +
444 +             @Override
445 +             public void rotateIfNeeded() throws IOException {
446 +                 if (rotationEnabled && !rotationPolicies.isEmpty()) {
447 +                     for (final RotationPolicy rotationPolicy : rotationPolicies) {
448 +                         if (rotationPolicy.shouldRotateFile(this)) {
449 +                             rotateNow();
450 +                             break;
451 +                         }
452 +                     }
453 +                 }
454 +                 if (!retentionPolicies.isEmpty()) {
455 +                     filesToDelete.clear();
456 +                     for (final RetentionPolicy retentionPolicy : retentionPolicies) {
457 +                         filesToDelete.addAll(retentionPolicy.deleteFiles(fileNamingPolicy));
458 +                     }
459 +                     if (!filesToDelete.isEmpty()) {
460 +                         for (final File file : filesToDelete) {
461 +                             if (!file.delete() && logger.isWarnEnabled()) {
462 +                                 logger.warn("Could not delete file {}", file.getAbsolutePath());
463 +                             }
464 +                         }
465 +                     }
466 +                 }
467 +             }
468 +
469 +             /**
470 +              * Rotates the underlying JSON audit file.
471 +              *
472 +              * @throws IOException error rotating file
473 +              */
474 +             void rotateNow() throws IOException {
475 +                 // close and rename current file
476 +                 fileChannel.close();
477 +                 final Path archivedFilePath = fileNamingPolicy.getNextName().toPath();
478 +                 Files.move(filePath, archivedFilePath);
479 +                 // create new file
480 +                 fileChannel = FileChannel.open(filePath, StandardOpenOption.CREATE_NEW,
481 +                         StandardOpenOption.WRITE);
482 +                 positionInFile = 0;
483 +                 lastRotationTime = DateTime.now(DateTimeZone.UTC);
484 +             }
485 +
486 +             @Override
487 +             public void close() throws IOException {
488 +                 fileChannel.close();
489 +             }
490 +
491 +             @Override
492 +             public void registerRotationHooks(RotationHooks rotationHooks) {
493 +                 // not implemented
494 +             }
495 +         }
496 +     }
497 +
498 + }

107 +     private void writeAndQueryEvents(final int eventCount, final boolean forceRotateDuringQuery) throws Exception {
108 +         final Path logDirectoryPath = Files.createTempDirectory(JsonAuditEventHandlerTest.class.getSimpleName());
109 +         AuditEventHandler handler = null;
110 +         try {
111 +             final JsonAuditEventHandlerConfiguration configuration = buildConfiguration(eventCount, logDirectoryPath);
112 +             if (forceRotateDuringQuery) {
113 +                 // enable rotation, but NOT any rotation policies, so that we can test the rotate-action
114 +                 configuration.getFileRotation().setRotationEnabled(true);

117 +             handler.startup();
118 +
119 +             // pre-populate with data and store generated IDs
120 +             String[] identifiers = generateAndPublishEvents(eventCount, handler);
121 +
122 +             // sleep to make sure async-publisher-thread finished all work
123 +             Thread.sleep(SLEEP_MILLIS);
124 +
125 +             if (forceRotateDuringQuery) {
126 +                 // only search for the last entry, when testing rotation
127 +                 identifiers = new String[]{identifiers[identifiers.length - 1]};
128 +             }

132 +                         resourceId);

136 +                 if (forceRotateDuringQuery) {
137 +                     // this rotate-action will NOT block the calling thread
138 +                     final ActionRequest actionRequest = Requests.newActionRequest(ACCESS, ROTATE_FILE_ACTION_NAME)

148 +             }

172 +     private String[] generateAndPublishEvents(final int eventCount, final AuditEventHandler handler) throws Exception {
173 +         final String[] identifiers = new String[eventCount];

177 +                     field("_id", id), field("timestamp", id), field("transactionId", id)));
178 +             identifiers[i] = handler.publishEvent(null, ACCESS, event).get().getId();
179 +         }

182 +         final ActionRequest actionRequest = Requests.newActionRequest(ACCESS, FLUSH_FILE_ACTION_NAME)
183 +                 .setAdditionalParameter(ACTION_PARAM_TARGET_HANDLER, "json");
184 +         handler.handleAction(null, ACCESS, actionRequest).getOrThrow();
185 +         return identifiers;
